			<h1>Icons and images</h1>
			<div class="breakout">
				<p>The MyService iconography style aligns with the Department of Veteran's Affairs personality and echoes other Australian Government service brands. Icons are in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flat_design" target="_blank" rel="external">flat design style</a>, meaning they use minimal stylistic elements.</p>
			</div>
			
			<h2>Icon features</h2>
			
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Consistent line weight</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-line-weight.svg" alt="Icon example of consistent line weight">
				</div>
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Geometric shapes</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-geometric.svg" alt="Icon example of gemoetric shapes">
				</div>
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Rounded corners</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-rounded.svg" alt="Icon example of rounded corners">
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<hr>
			
			<h2>Icon colours</h2>
			<p>An icon's default colour should be <font color="red">$grey</font> when used to add a visual element to content, and <font color="red">$blue</font> when used in a link. Icons can break from the default colour pattern but should never break from the MyService colour palette.</p>
			
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Default</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example sg-icon--small" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-color-default.svg" alt="Icon example of default colour">
				</div>
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Default link</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example sg-icon--small" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-color-link.svg" alt="Icon example of default link colour">
				</div>
				<div class="col-xs-4">
					<h4 class="heading-underline">Customised</h4>
					<img class="sg-icon-example sg-icon--small" src="../../../docs/images/styleguide/sg-ico-color-custom.svg" alt="Icon example of custom colour">
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<hr>

			<h2>Large icons</h2>
			<p>Icons can be used in large format to convey infographical information. An example is the 1, 2, 3 step feature on the unauthenticated home page.</p>
			
			<div class="example-box">
				<table class="table">
						<caption>Large icon example</caption>
						<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td><img src="/docs/images/howitworks-01.png" alt="Step 1" class="howitworks-img"></td>
							<td><img src="/docs/images/howitworks-02.png" alt="Step 2" class="howitworks-img"></td>
							<td><img src="/docs/images/howitworks-03.png" alt="Step 3" class="howitworks-img"></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="example-code">
								<code>&lt;img src=&quot;howitworks-01.png&quot; alt=&quot;Step 1&quot; class=&quot;howitworks-img&quot;&gt;</code>
							</td>
							<td class="example-code">
								<code>&lt;img src=&quot;howitworks-02.png&quot; alt=&quot;Step 2&quot; class=&quot;howitworks-img&quot;&gt;</code>
							</td>
							<td class="example-code">
								<code>&lt;img src=&quot;howitworks-03.png&quot; alt=&quot;Step 3&quot; class=&quot;howitworks-img&quot;&gt;</code>
							</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>	
			</div>

			<hr>
			
			<h2>Heading icons</h2>
			<p>Icons used alongside text in a heading can help convey a key message. For example, a green tick icon in a heading that reads 'You have submitted your claim' will assist the user in understanding they have just completed a process. Headings, <font color="red">&#60;h1&#62;</font> and <font color="red">&#60;h2&#62;</font>, are available for use with icons.</p></p>
			
			<div class="example-box">
				<table class="table">
					<caption>Heading icon example</caption>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td style="width: 40%">
								<h2><img src="../../../docs/images/ico-tick-green.svg" alt="Success tick icon"> Submitted</h2>
							</td>
							<td style="width: 60%" class="example-code">
								<code>&lt;h2&gt;&lt;img src="ico-tick-green.svg" alt="Success tick icon"&gt; Submitted&lt;/h2&gt;</code>
							</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
			
			<hr>
			
			<h2>Status icons</h2>
			<p>Status icons are smaller icons. They are the only icons that use additional colour to compliment design and textual context for conveying meaning. Status icons are used for indicating claim status and in <a href="styleguide-toast">toast messages</a>.</p></p>
			
			<div class="example-box">
				<table class="table">
						<caption>Status icon variations</caption>
						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td><p class="status-icon status-incomplete"> Incomplete</p></td>
								<td class="example-code">
										<code>&lt;p class=&quot;status-icon status-incomplete&quot;&gt;	Incomplete&lt;/p&gt;</code>
									</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
									<td><p class="status-icon status-approved"> Approved</p></td>
									<td class="example-code">
											<code>&lt;p class=&quot;status-icon status-approved&quot;&gt;	Approved&lt;/p&gt;</code>
										</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
